"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who said: 'We will not leave this place.'"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"His last breath floated upward"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like the smoke of a campfire going out,"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And the city he built"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Went on without him,"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Its streets filling with morning light."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Before Dawn"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Before Dawn — a poem honoring martyrs who died right before the founding of the new state. 'Dawn' metaphorically represents the peaceful liberation of Xinjiang in September 1949."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Verses from Junggar","》 · ","Volume II: The General and the City"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1984"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-2-2","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"She Too Became a Dark-Gold Wave of Signal"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Her radio signal traveled outward from the small room,"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the Tianshan night,"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the static of distance —"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"She too became a dark-gold wave of signal,"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"This woman of the frontier,"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who transmitted weather readings"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And troop positions"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And love letters"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across the crackle and hiss of the desert airwaves."}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Verses from Junggar","》 · ","Volume II: The General and the City"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1984"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-2-3","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"Prometheus Lit the Heavy Curtain of Night"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"annotation-term border-b border-dotted border-gray-400 cursor-help","title":"Prometheus — the Titan from Greek mythology who stole fire for humanity. The poet uses this metaphor to praise the revolutionary pioneers who brought light and hope to the darkness of Xinjiang.","children":["Prometheus",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":1}]]}]," lit the heavy curtain of night —"]}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Or was it the electrician from Shandong"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who strung the first power line"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across the Gurbantünggüt,"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Bringing electric light"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"To a place that had known"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Only candle, campfire, and star?"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"annotation-term border-b border-dotted border-gray-400 cursor-help","title":"Prometheus — the Titan from Greek mythology who stole fire for humanity. The poet uses this metaphor to praise the revolutionary pioneers who brought light and hope to the darkness of Xinjiang.","children":["Prometheus",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":1}]]}]," lit the heavy curtain of night,"]}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And the desert blinked"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In astonishment."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-5