,"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And these stars."}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Verses from Junggar","》 · ","Volume III: A Poet in the Gurbantünggüt"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1984"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","div","chapter-4",{"className":"mb-24 px-4","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-sans font-bold text-gray-300 uppercase tracking-widest pl-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-gray-100","children":"Volume IV: For Love, Baghdad Is Not Too Far"}],[["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-4-1","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"O, Nightingale"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"O, nightingale,"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Why do you sing in the red willow thickets"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"When the moon has already set?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Is your song for the darkness"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Or for the girl who listens"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"From her window in the barracks?"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"O, nightingale,"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The frontier has enough silence;"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Thank you for breaking it"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"With your small, wild voice."}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Nightingale"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Nightingale — a songbird frequently found in Xinjiang's red willow thickets. In Li Yu's poetry, it is an enduring symbol of love, lyricism, and melancholy, central to the Junggar imagery."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Verses from Junggar","》 · ","Volume IV: For Love, Baghdad Is Not Too Far"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1984"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-4-2","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"The Gentle, Unceasing Raindrops"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The gentle, unceasing raindrops"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Fall on the tin roof of the dugout,"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A rhythm soft as a lullaby,"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Soft as her voice when she said:"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"'I will wait for you.'"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Rain in the desert is a miracle,"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As rare as love,"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And as welcome."}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Verses from Junggar","》 · ","Volume IV: For Love, Baghdad Is Not Too Far"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1984"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-4-3","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"That Is a Crescent Moon behind the Dune"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That is a crescent moon behind the dune,"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Rising like a silver eyelash"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Above the sand's brown brow."}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Under this crescent moon"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"I write her name in the sand,"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Knowing the wind will erase it by morning,"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Knowing I will write it a